{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI","doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation"]]},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation\/linear","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/openswiftui\/animation\/linear"]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An animation that moves at a constant speed."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"linear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore9AnimationV","text":"Animation","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" }","kind":"text"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Return Value","level":2,"anchor":"return-value"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A linear animation with the default duration."}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A linear animation provides a mechanical feel to the motion because its","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"speed is consistent from start to finish of the animation. This","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"constant speed makes a linear animation ideal for animating the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"movement of objects where changes in the speed might feel awkward, such","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as with an activity indicator.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The following code shows an example of using linear animation to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"animate the movement of a circle as it moves between the leading and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"trailing edges of the view. The circle also animates its color change","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"as it moves across the view.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct ContentView: View {","    @State private var isActive = false","","    var body: some View {","        VStack(alignment: isActive ? .trailing : .leading) {","            Circle()","                .fill(isActive ? Color.red : Color.blue)","                .frame(width: 50, height: 50)","","            Button(\"Animate\") {","                withAnimation(.linear) {","                    isActive.toggle()","                }","            }","            .frame(maxWidth: .infinity)","        }","    }","}"],"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"linear"},{"type":"text","text":" animation has a default duration of 0.35 seconds. To"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"specify a different duration, use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Animation\/linear(duration:)"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","platforms":[{"name":"iOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"macOS","introducedAt":"10.15","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"tvOS","introducedAt":"13.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"visionOS","introducedAt":"1.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false},{"name":"watchOS","introducedAt":"6.0","deprecated":false,"unavailable":false,"beta":false}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"static"},{"kind":"text","